items.title: Stephen Miller Says 'History Will Record' Trump's Tariffs As The Start Of Saving The West From China's Economic Domination'
items.description: A new round of tariff hikes from President Donald Trump's administration has reignited trade tensions between the world's two largest economies. "History will record that the actions President Trump has taken in recent days were the beginning of saving the West from complete economic domination by another power," White House Deputy Chief of Staff Stephen Miller said in an April 13 interview on Fox News, referring to China's growing influence over global supply chains.
